    "title": "SAIL is Hiring: Quality Control Engineer (Mid-Level)",
    "description": "If you're a passionate Quality Control Engineer with drive and ambition, SAIL in Bengaluru is the place for you. We're growing fast and need talented people to grow with us.\n\nAbout SAIL:\nSAIL is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Ensure compliance with safety regulations and factory acts\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n• Manage supplier quality audits and vendor development\n• Implement 5S, Kaizen, and Six Sigma practices on the shop floor\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Maintain accurate production records and prepare daily reports\n• Monitor equipment performance and coordinate preventive maintenance\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Chartered Accountant (ICAI)\n• 1-3 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in PPAP\n• Proficiency in SAP MM/PP\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n• Proficiency in TPM\n• Proficiency in APQP\n• Proficiency in PLC/SCADA\n• Proficiency in Project Management\n• Proficiency in Quality Control\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Referral bonus program\n• Flexible working hours\n• Salary Range: 4 LPA - 9 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Bengaluru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with SAIL!",
